英语 英语会说吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}No, English. English, perhaps.{\r}

331
00:28:09,100 --> 00:28:10,499
抱歉 你是谁？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I'm sorry, who are you?{\r}

332
00:28:10,801 --> 00:28:16,467
我是卡门拉 我是王中之王
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I am Kahmunrah, the great king of the great kings,{\r}

333
00:28:16,574 --> 00:28:19,941
从最黑暗的古老历史深处
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}and from the darkest depths of ancient history,{\r}

334
00:28:20,011 --> 00:28:23,913
我死而复生！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I have come back to life!{\r}

335
00:28:27,818 --> 00:28:30,878
你大概没听清我的话
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Perhaps you did not hear what I just said.{\r}

336
00:28:30,955 --> 00:28:36,450
我是古老埃及的法老 我曾经死去
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I am a centuries-old Egyptian Pharaoh. I was dead,{\r}

337
00:28:36,527 --> 00:28:40,964
但是现在 我死而复生！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}but now I have come back to life!{\r}

338
00:28:41,699 --> 00:28:44,668
哦 是 我听清了 我明白你的意思 欢迎回来！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Yeah, no. I heard that. I got that. Welcome back.{\r}

339
00:28:48,172 --> 00:28:53,166
- 你是谁？ - 戴利设备的拉瑞・戴利
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}- Who are you? - Larry Daley. Daley Devices?{\r}

340
00:28:53,277 --> 00:28:57,373
我公司在纽约市 很有趣 我还认识你弟弟阿卡曼拉
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}It's up in New York. It's funny, I know your brother, Ahkmenrah.{\r}

341
00:28:57,481 --> 00:28:58,778
- 是吗？ - 是的
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}- Do you? - Yeah.{\r}

342
00:28:58,849 --> 00:29:02,546
他说他认识我弟弟 最受宠的儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}He knows baby brother. The favorite son.{\r}

343
00:29:02,653 --> 00:29:05,144
- 对 是个好孩子 - 谁说不是呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}- Yeah, good kid. - Isn't he just?{\r}

344
00:29:05,523 --> 00:29:08,321
知道吗 妈妈和爸爸总是把所有最好的给他
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}You know, Mother and Father always gave him the best of everything,{\r}

345
00:29:08,392 --> 00:29:11,623
我说的是所有 甚至包括王位
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}and I do mean everything. They even gave him the throne.{\r}

346
00:29:12,163 --> 00:29:14,495
我才应该是王位继承人！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}The throne which was rightfully mine!{\r}

347
00:29:15,366 --> 00:29:17,960
- 他没提过这事 - 我打赌他不会说
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}- He never mentioned that. - I'll just bet he didn't.{\r}

348
00:29:18,035 --> 00:29:24,406
不过卡门拉时代现在来临了 因为我死而复…
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Well, now begins the era of Kahmunrah, because I have come back to...{\r}

349
00:29:24,508 --> 00:29:26,373
算了 把金牌给我
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Never mind, just hand me the tablet.{\r}

350
00:29:26,477 --> 00:29:28,672
别给他 铁人！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}- Don't give it to him, Gigantor! - Keep him away!{\r}

351
00:29:28,746 --> 00:29:31,237
安静！你们给我安静！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Silence! Silence in there, please!{\r}

352
00:29:32,049 --> 00:29:35,485
- 别逼我进去！ - 我不会保持沉默！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}- Don't make me come in there! - No! I won't be muzzled!{\r}

353
00:29:35,719 --> 00:29:38,779
听着 这金牌所拥有的力量
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Look, that tablet is more powerful{\r}

354
00:29:38,856 --> 00:29:43,350
是你这个戴利设备的拉瑞・戴利 根本无法想象的
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}than you, Larry Daley of Daley Devices, can possibly imagine.{\r}

355
00:29:43,594 --> 00:29:47,530
恢复生命只是其中一个小把戏
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Bringing things back to life is just a parlor trick.{\r}

356
00:29:47,598 --> 00:29:50,829
有了它 我就可以开启尘封的地下世界之门
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}With it, I shall unlock the Gate to the Underworld{\r}

357
00:29:50,901 --> 00:29:54,530
从死亡之地召回我的军队
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}and bring forth my army from the Land of the Dead.{\r}

358
00:29:54,605 --> 00:29:57,540
如果不麻烦的话…
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}So, if it's not too much trouble...{\r}

359
00:30:00,511 --> 00:30:02,445
…把它给我
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}...hand it over.{\r}

360
00:30:05,216 --> 00:30:06,581
好吧 给你
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Okay, here you go.{\r}

361
00:30:08,085 --> 00:30:09,677
明智的选择
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Wise decision.{\r}

362
00:30:12,923 --> 00:30:15,687
是啊 很抱歉 我以为你是想要那个魔方 不过…
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Yeah, I know. I'm sorry, I thought you wanted the Cube, but...{\r}

363
00:30:19,230 --> 00:30:20,720
魔方？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}The Cube?{\r}

364
00:30:21,966 --> 00:30:24,833
魔法立方体
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}The Cube of Rubik.{\r}

365
00:30:27,638 --> 00:30:33,304
好吧 这个魔法立方体是干什么的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}All right, what is this Cube of Rubik, then?{\r}

366
00:30:33,410 --> 00:30:38,347
就是魔方 那个可以把你的敌人化成灰的魔方
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}The Cube. You know, the one that turns all who oppose you to dust?{\r}

367
00:30:38,949 --> 00:30:41,349
有这个玩意儿吗？随便吧 总之…
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}That one? Whatever. I thought...{\r}

368
00:30:41,452 --> 00:30:43,443
是我不好 顺便说一句
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}It was my bad, 'cause... You know what? By the way,{\r}

369
00:30:43,521 --> 00:30:45,148
你弟弟也不想搞得这么砸
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}your brother didn't want to mess with it, either.{\r}

370
00:30:45,256 --> 00:30:46,587
他不想两败俱伤
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Yeah, he wanted to play it safe, too.{\r}

371
00:30:46,657 --> 00:30:49,683
只是 你看上去像比他厉害些 所以我…
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Just, you sort of struck me as a next-level sort of guy, so I was...{\r}

372
00:30:51,829 --> 00:30:54,161
我不是我弟弟 拉瑞
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I am not my brother, Larry.{\r}

373
00:30:54,765 --> 00:30:58,724
只需一眨眼的功夫 我就能杀光你和你的朋友们
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I will kill you and your friends in the blink of an eye.{\r}

374
00:31:01,138 --> 00:31:04,437
带我去那个魔法立方体
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Now take me to this Cube of Rubik.{\r}

375
00:31:06,977 --> 00:31:08,842
- 就在这儿 - 打开
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}- Here it is. - Open it.{\r}

376
00:31:38,342 --> 00:31:40,333
回来！把金牌还给我！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Come back here! Come back here with my tablet!{\r}

377
00:31:40,411 --> 00:31:41,969
你朋友还在我手上！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I still have your friends!{\r}

378
00:32:20,985 --> 00:32:22,976
- 你来开！ - 什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}- Take the wheel! - What?{\r}

379
00:32:23,087 --> 00:32:26,579
我说你来开 打起来了 打起来了 我爱它
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I said, take the wheel! Oh, we're in it now! I love it! I love it!{\r}

380
00:32:27,057 --> 00:32:28,718
笔直往前 其他我来对付
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Just keep her straight, I'll handle the rest.{\r}

381
00:32:28,792 --> 00:32:30,817
前进！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Now, charge!{\r}

382
00:32:37,201 --> 00:32:39,465
好吧 接下去你有什么计划？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Okay, so what's the plan here?{\r}

383
00:32:39,465 --> 00:32:41,729
我们是美国人！我们从不计划 我们是行动家！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}We're Americans! We don't plan, we do!{\r}

384
00:32:41,805 --> 00:32:43,568
不要减速！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Now hold on!{\r}

385
00:32:53,917 --> 00:32:58,547
看到没有？先行而后思 每次都管用！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}See that? Act first, think later! Works every time!{\r}

386
00:32:58,622 --> 00:32:59,987
我可是好手！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}You're in good hands!{\r}

387
00:33:00,124 --> 00:33:03,821
美国第七骑兵队将军 乔治・阿姆斯特朗・卡斯特
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}General George A. Custer of the Fighting U.S. 7th Cavalry,{\r}

388
00:33:03,927 --> 00:33:05,554
为您效劳
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}at your service.{\r}

389
00:33:09,767 --> 00:33:12,292
我没事 继续开 笨蛋
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I'm good, I'm good! Fly, you fool!{\r}

390
00:33:22,813 --> 00:33:24,178
你们吵什么吵 牛仔？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}What's the rumpus, ace?{\r}

391
00:33:24,281 --> 00:33:25,612
听着 女士 你能让开吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Look, lady, could you get out of the way?{\r}

392
00:33:25,683 --> 00:33:28,277
女士？你叫谁女士？ 我是阿梅莉亚
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Lady? Who are you calling lady? The name is Amelia.{\r}

393
00:33:34,825 --> 00:33:37,350
阿梅莉亚・埃尔哈特 我想你听说过我吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Amelia Earhart! Perhaps you've heard of me?{\r}

394
00:33:37,461 --> 00:33:40,225
哦 是啊 著名飞行员什么的吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Oh, right. You're a famous pilot or whatever.{\r}

395
00:33:40,331 --> 00:33:43,027
飞行员？ 我可是第一个飞越大西洋的女性
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Pilot? I was the first woman to fly the Atlantic!{\r}

396
00:33:43,133 --> 00:33:44,725
第一个荣获飞行十字勋章的女性
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}First woman to receive the Flying Cross,{\r}

397
00:33:44,835 --> 00:33:47,827
第一个驾驶自转旋翼机 飞越美国48个州的女飞行员
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}first woman to fly across the 48 states in a gyroprop.{\r}

398
00:33:47,905 --> 00:33:50,738
如果你愿意的话请先放下你那副永远紧张兮兮的嘴脸
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Now if you'd wipe that perhaps-permanent look of alarm off your kisser,{\r}

399
00:33:50,841 --> 00:33:55,039
请告诉我我现在在哪儿 非常感谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I was wondering if you might be so kind as to tell me exactly where I am.{\r}

400
00:33:55,112 --> 00:33:57,512
你在一个博物馆 准确点是博物馆下面
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}You're in a museum. Or, actually, under it.{\r}

401
00:33:57,581 --> 00:34:00,379
我现在是众矢之的
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}And I'm in kind of a dangerous situation right now,{\r}

402
00:34:00,451 --> 00:34:02,919
所以你最好躲到离我远点的地方
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}so you might not want to be anywhere near me.{\r}

403
00:34:05,422 --> 00:34:07,390
- 你动作真快 - 你叫什么 飞行员？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}- Wow, you're fast. - What's your name, flyboy?{\r}

404
00:34:08,092 --> 00:34:10,219
我叫拉瑞・戴利
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}My name is Larry Daley.{\r}

405
00:34:10,728 --> 00:34:13,196
拉瑞・戴利 你给我听好了
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Well, Larry Daley, in case you weren't listening,{\r}

406
00:34:13,263 --> 00:34:15,390
我可不是个胆小怕事的人
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I'm not one to shy away from danger.{\r}

407
00:34:16,734 --> 00:34:19,225
那矛呢 你怕不怕矛呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}How about spears? Are you one to shy away from spears?{\r}

408
00:34:20,604 --> 00:34:24,096
让我们找点乐子 机长！ 痛快玩一场吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Let's ankle, skipper! Now we're gonna have some fun.{\r}

409
00:34:27,711 --> 00:34:31,875
98 99 完美
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Ninety-eight, ninety-nine, bingo!{\r}

410
00:34:34,151 --> 00:34:35,743
像金羊毛一样
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Like a Golden Fleece.{\r}

411
00:34:36,653 --> 00:34:40,248
听着 士兵们 当你们的敌人抓住我的时候
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}All right, troops, when your enemies captured me,{\r}

412
00:34:40,324 --> 00:34:42,485
他们也就成了我的瓮中之鳖
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}they made themselves my enemies as well.{\r}

413
00:34:43,260 --> 00:34:45,956
大错误 一个大错误
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Big mistake. Big mistake.{\r}

414
00:34:48,632 --> 00:34:50,759
我的计划是这样的
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}All right, here's the plan.{\r}

415
00:34:51,602 --> 00:34:55,470
吹响三声号角 我会大声宣布：“攻击！”
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}On the third bugle blast, I shall loudly announce, "Attack!"{\r}

416
00:34:58,409 --> 00:35:03,676
然后我们全体跳出这个箱子
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}At which point, we will all jump out of this box{\r}

417
00:35:05,416 --> 00:35:06,974
开始攻击
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}and attack.{\r}

418
00:35:13,590 --> 00:35:17,458
很震撼吧 觉得怎么样？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Mind bomb. What do you think?{\r}

419
00:35:19,963 --> 00:35:22,454
你说 萨什么什么…
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}You, Sacaja...{\r}

420
00:35:22,533 --> 00:35:23,761
那不是我的名字
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}That is not my name.{\r}

421
00:35:23,834 --> 00:35:25,859
- 萨卡娅米尔 - 不是
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}- Sacajamea. - No.{\r}

422
00:35:25,969 --> 00:35:28,199
- 变态 娘娘腔（俚语） - 不是
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}- Sack-in-a-box. - No.{\r}

423
00:35:28,305 --> 00:35:29,670
（西班牙文5月5日 一个节日）
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Cinco de Mayo.{\r}

424
00:35:29,670 --> 00:35:31,035
我知道你是个著名的将军…
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I know you are a famous general...{\r}

425
00:35:31,141 --> 00:35:33,473
那算不上什么 我也是个普通人 和你一样
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}That's all right, that's all right. I'm a person, just like you.{\r}

426
00:35:34,144 --> 00:35:36,704
当你大叫“攻击”的时候
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}But won't yelling, "Attack!" Alert the enemy{\r}

427
00:35:36,814 --> 00:35:38,304
敌人不就立刻知道我们要攻击了吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}that we are about to attack?{\r}

428
00:35:38,816 --> 00:35:40,147
什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}What?{\r}

429
00:35:48,659 --> 00:35:50,559
哦 也许你说的对
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Yeah, I guess so.{\r}

430
00:35:56,567 --> 00:35:58,432
你很受欢迎嘛 戴利先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}You're quite the popular fellow, Mr. Daley.{\r}

431
00:35:58,502 --> 00:35:59,992
你干嘛不直接逃走？
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Why don't you just skedaddle?{\r}

432
00:36:00,070 --> 00:36:02,038
我不能逃 我的朋友还在他们手上
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I can't skedaddle. My friends are being held down there.{\r}

433
00:36:02,139 --> 00:36:04,835
我得去救他们 得另找一条路下去
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I got to go get them. I got to find another way down.{\r}

434
00:36:15,919 --> 00:36:17,386
以前没见过
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}This is new.{\r}

435
00:36:23,727 --> 00:36:26,753
没事 我不会伤害你们
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Hey, it's all right. I don't want to hurt you.{\r}

436
00:36:29,533 --> 00:36:31,524
我想他们怕的不是你 戴利先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I don't think it's you they're afraid of, Mr. Daley.{\r}

437
00:36:38,375 --> 00:36:40,275
交换 谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Trade you. Thanks.{\r}

438
00:36:40,878 --> 00:36:44,211
退后 给我退后！
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Back off! Just back off!{\r}

439
00:36:45,415 --> 00:36:47,042
小心被我叉到
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}I will fork you!{\r}

440
00:36:47,384 --> 00:36:48,874
别轻举妄动
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}How about you, huh?{\r}

441
00:36:51,722 --> 00:36:53,417
男人就是不如女人
{\fscx75\fscy75\3c&HFF0000&}Never send a boy to do a woman's job.{\r}

